# =============================================================================
# codex backend — BYO (bring-your-own) OpenAI-compatible endpoint + key.
#
#   cp config/codex.env.example config/codex.env   # then edit config/codex.env
#
# codex (the workers + the verifier) can run one of two ways:
#   - api     : point codex at any OpenAI-compatible Responses endpoint you own
#               (Azure OpenAI, OpenAI, a proxy, …). Fill the values below, then
#               `scripts/setup-codex.sh api` writes the matching model_provider.
#   - chatgpt : use YOUR ChatGPT Pro/Plus subscription — set CODEX_BACKEND=chatgpt
#               in config/danus.env and run `scripts/setup-codex.sh login`.
#
# This file is gitignored (only *.example is committed). NEVER commit a real key.
# `scripts/env.sh` sources it first in the config chain, so every line must be
# valid shell — leave the api values COMMENTED for the chatgpt-login path (an
# uncommented placeholder like `<your endpoint>` is a shell redirect and would
# break sourcing). Uncomment + fill them only for the `api` backend.
# =============================================================================

# ---- api path: uncomment + fill, then `scripts/setup-codex.sh api` ----------
#CODEX_BACKEND=api
#CODEX_API_BASE_URL=https://your.openai.azure.com/openai/v1/
#CODEX_API_MODEL=gpt-5.5
#DANUS_CODEX_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
